cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.IR 

This paper is about using deep learning for tumor detection in medical images, specifically contrast-enhanced CT images of pancreatic cancer. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a novel framework that involves feature extraction, fusion, and interaction, which suggests that it could fall under cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the use of medical images could also place it under cs.MM (Multimedia) or cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
